examples.en: She was cited for reckless driving.
He cited various reasons for his behavior.
Adultery is often cited as grounds for divorce.
He cited Joan of Arc as the exemplar of courage.
After his death, the soldier was cited for bravery.
Two managers had been cited for similar infractions.
He cited the First Amendment guarantee of free speech.
The judge cited a 1956 Supreme Court ruling in her decision.
She cited a number of recent examples to support her theory.
The museum had often been cited as an example of successful fund-raising.
The report cited a lack of cooperation between state and local officials.
The statute does not seem to support the assertions for which it was cited.
She cited a series of statistics to dramatize the seriousness of the problem.
He cited evidence suggesting she was in the area when the crime was committed.
Milton Friedman is usually cited as the leading American protagonist of monetarism.
The movie star's violet eyes are frequently cited as the source of her cinematic witchery.
The Louisiana Purchase is cited by many historians as one of the most signal events in American history.
The golden rule is often cited as the epitome of moral conduct: Do unto others as you would have them do unto you.
